I'm not an expert here, but it seems like st_join from the sf package does what you need:

library(sf)
species       <- st_read('species.shp')
ecosystem <- st_read('ecosystem.shp')
species       <- st_join(species, ecosystem)

This should give you a row for each species x ecosystem that the species appears in. This is a left join so the spatial data is still the species distribution map. It seems fast too.

Regards,

Jason

